<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9695456336105></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9695456336105><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=9695456336105>FD Practice</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=9695456336105#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Sep 21st 10:13 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just something I noticed. Not sure if it will work for others, but it seemed to raise my FD faster than just staying in one area. 1) Go to Oasis 2) Find the 2 pillars in the water. I believe the first is called P1 and is near the dock and the other is north of the first(P2).<br>3) What I did at this point was stand on either pillar at the top as high as I could and used FD.<br>It usually went up within 10 tries. Then after 1 or 2 points I swam to the other pillar and repeated the process back and forth. Staying in one place only and using FD seemed to take about 30-40+ tries to gain a point. As I said it may not work, but it did for me, and I gained a good amount of swimming skill as well. Hope it works and good luck my fellow brothers and sisters.<br><br>Shinijo Yodama<br>Nameless<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
