	   <tr><td colspan=2>The idea that monks are awesome pullers is only true after they get good at Feign Death. Because if they accidently get a train going, they can Feign Death and "abort" the pull. If it succeeds, the mobs will stop attacking and eventually mosy back to do whatever it is they were doing before you came along. <br>Also, during the fight, if you're getting your butt kicked and the monster won't stop attacking you, you can FD and it'll start picking on someone else (again, assuming you succeed) I think if you're fighitng orcs in oasis, you either don't have FD yet or just learned it and arean't very good at it. Monks can dish out a good ammount of damage, but they can't take much. So if you don't have FD, and don't have a healer in your group, you'd be best off to leave the pulling to those who can take damage better<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
