	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Nov 1st 2:30 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'd like to offer a possible explanation from a shammie's point of view for your bad experience while feigning. <br><br> If you were attempting to feign while the sham was healing you the resulting hp increase causes the mob to see through your feign.  In other words, it sees you "faking" your death because it sees the magic surrounding you from the healing spell cast.  It will happen when you attempt to bind a wound on a feigned monkey/NEC/SK as well. <br><br>You will need to remind your group members not to cast on you when you FD to prevent this in the future.<br><br>If you have a bubble of health remaining it might cause a mob to frenzy on you.  However, you CAN still feign and convince the mob you have died, but the advice given in other areas of these posts addresses various techniques used to enhance your chances for success.<br><br>Good luck, young monkey!<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
