	   <tr><td colspan=2> I decided to try somewhere new tonight, after getting sick and tired of getting sand in my tunic in Oasis, so I headed up to Rivervale with the hopes of a bind and a quick jaunt to the Gorge. That turned out to be harder than I thought with all the muddites ganging up on me, so I zoned into East Karana, and I've gotta tell you, it was great experience. <br> I was reading something today that Gordon posted about getting more experience in sparsely populated zones than you would in more crowded zones, and I'm wondering if this doesn't qualify. I fought mostly lions and gorge hounds, never lost too much hp, and gained exp. very quickly. So if you're in the area, I'd recommend you check it out. I was in the area next to the gorge, which has a nice little set of houses on the left that you can buy bandages from and sell your loot to, though if you're worried about dying, you might want to stick near the bridge to North Karana. Anyway, I plan to stick with that area for another few days and see how it goes. Good luck!<br>&nbsp;<br>Beleni<br>Lowly Monk on Karana</td></tr>
