	   <tr><td colspan=2>I had the same problem as you did, and here's something that I didn't know at first, but I did learn afterwards.<br><br><br>If it says that you've fallen to the ground, it means you've failed.<br><br>I myself was wondering what was a good FD and what was a bad FD for a couple of levels. Another sign of a succesfully FD is if you hear that nice little "You're dead" music after doing the FD. Come on, you know which music I'm talking about. Seems that only works if you practice it outside though...<br><br>Another thing to know: You can practice FD when you have already Feigned Death (thus removing the annoying "press sit" middle phase). Don't do that outdoors however, because if you do an unsuccesful FD after you've done a succesful FD, then you cancel the effects of your previous FD... got it? well?<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
