	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you want to minimize that loss even a bit more, find a friendly Shaman to cast one of their charisma-enhancing spells before you either make the trek to an in-zone merchant or go back to town. Spirit of Snake is pretty good, but Alluring Aura (I think thats it) is wonderful! I believe that it adds something like 25 points to your charisma, and that can make a serious difference in dealing with merchants. <br><br>To take the suggestion of buying jewelry to use up some coin and reduce weight, why not try to purchase charisma-enhancing jewelry whenever possible. When you go to sell, equip it to raise that CHA to get better prices, ending the transaction by selling the CHA jewelry that you are wearing to the merchie- that way, you'll get the benefit of the increased CHA score when the price is set. CHA jewelry is downright CHEAP and is generally available in any zone that has a sizable PC population.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
