	   <tr><td colspan=2>The Best place I've found to raise safe fall, without taking any damage is in Lake Rathe.  The hill directly behind that monk Johnas.  You can raise your safe fall 5 points in under 2 minutes there.  Just run to the top and run down...<br><br>Here are some other Good places...<br>   The Side of the Ridge in East Karana on the way to high pass.  Be sure to do this on the lower side after the trail does the cross-over.  On the higher side it's a long fall with no chance to stop yourself midway.  <br>   Several Pillars in the Oasis Area.<br>   Several Cliff Sides in the Cauldron area before Unrest.<br><br>Another good place is in The Gorge while waiting for the alchemist to spawn.  You can make as many skill checks as you want while waiting on that 75 minute timer to get the spawn.<br><br>What you're looking for is a single place where you run down and make 3-4 skill checks right after each other.  Avoid at all costs those ramps where you run and drop, run around and drop again, making 1 skill check at each pass.  This is a complete waste of time which could be better used killing things.<br>   Also be careful at the lower levels, some of the recommend places will get you killed if your safe fall isn't high enough to start with.<br><br>Also the best way to increase weapon skills and bind wound skill is to find some blue and beat the ever living snot out of it with the weapon skill of choice...then after hitting it for 5 minutes or so for 1-2 points damage feign and bind all your wounds, then repeat as necessary. I got 2 levels increasing my 1-hb from 0 when I first started practicing it at level 26.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
