<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=967926413824></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f967926413824><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=967926413824>RE: Best place to raise safe fall</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=967926413824#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=759><span id=Scholar>Adiemus</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>48 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Sep 2nd 4:26 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.05]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Let me add a threef personal choice locations for rasing that safe fall skill:<br><br>North Ro- right as you exit the tunnel from east commons, there are walls to either side of you, as well as a pillar directly in front. You can hang a quick left and run up the wall, then run down the wall toward the pillar, up the pillar, down the pillar and up the right hand wall. I have gotten a point once each time down , but that is far from typical. The idea here is to practice the skill as many times as possible in the smallest area possible, preferably an area where you'll not be bothered by MoBs. This one qualifies on all three points. One warning: DO NOT HAVE SoW! You WILL die!<br><br>Second one is the walls on the Nek Forest side of East Commons, particularly on the Freeport side of the first Inn. Nothing will bother you here, and the wall is certainly high enough for you to have multiple practice attempts each time down. SoW here is an iffy proposition- you can practice more often, but you can take a fair amount of damage if you fail.<br><br>Lastly, for my Iksar Brethren (and Sistren) out there, try this one.  In the center of the Field of Bone is the Pit, as it has come to be called. To enter the pit, there are many ramps that are bordered on either side by the actual wall of the pit. Go on top of the ramp walls about a third of the way out and simply run off the top. With luck, you will have practiced Safe Fall and not taken any damage. If you've hurt yourself, regen takes care of that pretty quickly. You can also practice on the walls of the FoB zone, again using SoW if you can get one, but my experience has been that the ramp walls yield more successes at practicing SF than do the zone walls.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
