<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96708967025257></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96708967025257><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=96708967025257>2hb damage bonus</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=96708967025257#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=950><span id= >Korthil</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>6 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 24th 12:01 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Aka, why the Runed Fighters Staff is so damned good.<br><br>Allright.  The 2hb damage bonus works in a similar fashion as the 1hb (read my post, Tutorial on which weapons in which hand).  The formula is a little different:<br>bonus=(level-7)/3<br><br>So, same as 1hbs in the primary hand, delay is king.  Everyone goes gaga over the Tranquil Staff (and I admit, it's impressive), but let's not forget the underdog, the Runed Fighters Staff.  Both have about the same dmg/delay ratio (t-staff at 29/30 and RFS at 19/20), but the RFS is much faster.  By the time you get either of these weapons, you should have some haste item.  If you don't, _get one_.  <br><br>haste items work on a percentage, same way ratio calcs do...but the addition of a constant damage bonus gives the RFS an edge, especially when paired with a FBSS.  The consensus among monks that have both to compare (and have logged/parsed damage over time, including proc on t-staff) is the the RFS outdamages the T-Staff, and (based on damage calcs vs. delay) outdamages the (mythical) Ton Po's Bo Staff of Understanding, even with it's jaw-dropping 44dmg/40delay.  Yes, the damage bonus is that important!<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br><br>--Korthil</td></tr>
